==English==

===Etymology===

{{etyl|LL.}} {{term|perfunctorius}}, from the past participial stem of {{term||[[perfungor]], perfunct-|perform, carry through}}, from {{term|per-}} + {{term|fungor}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/pəˈfʌŋk.tɹɪ/}}, {{SAMPA|/p@"VNk.t@r.I/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/pɚˈfʌŋ.tɚ.i/}}
* {{audio|en-us-perfunctory.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Performed out of [[routine]] and with little [[care]].
#: ''He did a '''perfunctory''' job cleaning his dad's car, finishing quickly but leaving a few spots still dirty.''
#* '''1992''', Peter Bowbrick, ''The Economics of Quality, Grades, and Brands'', [http://books.google.ca/books?id=zygOAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA55&dq=%22perfunctory%22 p. 55],
#*: Alternatively it may mean that a '''perfunctory''' search is enough to ensure that a purchase is acceptable, so less search is carried out.

